<dl id="n40110a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40110a">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40110a"> 110(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> from Dan / to Bare Shaba </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: &ldquo;From Dan to Beersheba&rdquo; is a biblical phrase used nine times in the Hebrew Bible to refer to the settled areas of the Tribes of Israel between Dan in the North and Beersheba in the South. <font color="green">[The term contributed to the position that was used by British politicians during negotiation of the British Mandate for Palestine following World War I.]</font> Thus, 2 Samuel 3:10 during the war between Ish-bosheth and his brother-in-law David following the death of Saul &ldquo;&hellip; and transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and establish David&apos;s throne over Israel and Judah from Dan to Beersheba.&rdquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
